(13, 'Python Casting', 'python-casting', '<h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Specify a Variable Type</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">There may be times when you want to specify a type on to a variable. This can be done with casting. Python is an object-orientated language, and as such it uses classes to define data types, including its primitive types.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">Casting in python is therefore done using constructor functions:</p><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 15.75px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3); padding-left: 4px; padding-right: 4px;\">int()</span>&nbsp;- constructs an integer number from an integer literal, a float literal (by removing all decimals), or a string literal (providing the string represents a whole number)</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 15.75px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3); padding-left: 4px; padding-right: 4px;\">float()</span>&nbsp;- constructs a float number from an integer literal, a float literal or a string literal (providing the string represents a float or an integer)</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 15.75px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3); padding-left: 4px; padding-right: 4px;\">str()</span>&nbsp;- constructs a string from a wide variety of data types, including strings, integer literals and float literals</li></ul><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example<br></h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">Integers:</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\"><span class=\"pythoncolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: black;\"><span class=\"commentcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: green;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">x =&nbsp;</span><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">int</span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">(</span><span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\">1</span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span class=\"commentcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"># x will be 1<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"></span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">y =&nbsp;</span><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">int</span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">(</span><span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\