rit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 15.75px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3);\">while</code>&nbsp;loops in our&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.w3schools.com/python/python_while_loops.asp\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: inherit;\">Python While Loops</a>&nbsp;Chapter.</p><hr style=\"margin-right: -16px; margin-left: -16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Looping Using List Comprehension</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">List Comprehension offers the shortest syntax for looping through lists:</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">A short hand&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 15.75px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3);\">for</code>&nbsp;loop that will print all items in a list:</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">thislist = [<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"apple\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"banana\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"cherry\"</span>]<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">[<span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(x)&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">for</span>&nbsp;x&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">in</span>&nbsp;thislist]<br></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"https://www.w3schools.com/python/trypython.asp?filename=demo_list_loop_comprehensive\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Try it Yourself »</a></div><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">Learn more about list comprehension in the next chapter:&nbsp;List Comprehension.<a href=\"https://www.w3schools.com/python/python_lists_comprehension.asp\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: inherit;\"></a></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2023-06-15 12:15:28'),
(23, 'Python - List Comprehension', 'python-list-comprehension', '<h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">List Comprehension</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">List comprehension offers a shorter syntax when you want to create a new list based on the values of an existing list.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">Example:</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">Based on a list of fruits, you want a new list, containing only the fruits with the letter \"a\" in the name.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">Without list comprehension you will have to write a&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 15.75px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3);\">for</code>&nbsp;statement with a conditional test inside:</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example<br></h3><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">fruits = [<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"apple\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"banana\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"cherry\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"kiwi\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"mango\"</span>]<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">newlist = []<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">for</span>&nbsp;x&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">in</span>&nbsp;fruits:<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">if</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"a\"</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">in</span>&nbsp;x:<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span>newlist.append(x)<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(newlist)<br></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"https://www.w3schools.com/python/trypython.asp?filename=demo_list_without_comprehension\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Try it Yourself »</a></div><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">With list comprehension you can do all that with only one line of code:</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example</h3><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">fruits = [<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"apple\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"banana\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"cherry\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"kiwi\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"mango\"</span>]<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">newlist = [x&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">for</span>&nbsp;x&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">in</span>&nbsp;fruits&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">if</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"a\"</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">in</span>&nbsp;x]<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(newlist)<br></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"https://www.w3schools.com/python/trypython.asp?filename=demo_list_comprehension\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Try it Yourself »</a></div><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The Syntax</h2><div class=\"w3-codeline notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: white; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; padding: 15px; border-left-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 15px;\">newlist = [<em style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">expression</em>&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">for</span>&nbsp;<em style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">item</em>&nbsp;<