(28, 'Python Tuples', 'python-tuples', '<div class=\"w3-codeline notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: white; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; padding: 15px; border-left-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 15px;\">mytuple = (<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"apple\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"banana\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"cherry\"</span>)<br></div><hr style=\"margin-right: -16px; margin-left: -16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Tuple</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">Tuples are used to store multiple items in a single variable.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">Tuple is one of 4 built-in data types in Python used to store collections of data, the other 3 are&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.w3schools.com/python/python_lists.asp\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: inherit;\">List</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.w3schools.com/python/python_sets.asp\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: inherit;\">Set</a>, and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.w3schools.com/python/python_dictionaries.asp\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: inherit;\">Dictionary</a>, all with different qualities and usage.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">A tuple is a collection w