(31, 'Python - Unpack Tuples', 'python-unpack-tuples', '<h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Unpacking a Tuple</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">When we create a tuple, we normally assign values to it. This is called \"packing\" a tuple:</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example<br></h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">Packing a tuple:</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\"><span class=\"pythoncolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: black;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">fruits = (</span><span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"apple\"</span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">,&nbsp;</span><span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"banana\"</span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">,&nbsp;</span><span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"cherry\"</span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">)</span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span></span></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"https://www.w3schools.com/python/trypython.asp?filename=demo_tuple_packing\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Try it Yourself »</a></div><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">But, in Python, we are also allowed to extract the values back into variables. This is called \"unpacking\":</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">Unpacking a tuple:</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">fruits = (<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"apple\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"banana\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"cherry\"</span>)<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span>(green, yellow, red) = fruits<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(green)<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(yellow)<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(red)<br></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"https://www.w3schools.com/python/trypython.asp?filename=demo_tuple_unpacking\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Try it Yourself »</a></div><div class=\"w3-panel w3-note\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; padding: 16px 32px; margin: 24px -32px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 204); border-left: none; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bolder;\">Note:</span>&nbsp;The number of variables must match the number of values in the tuple, if not, you must use an asterisk to collect the remaining values as a list.</p></div><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Using Asterisk<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 33.6px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3);\">*</code></h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">If the number of variables is less than the number of values, you can add an&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 15.75px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3);\">*</code>&nbsp;to the variable name and the values will be assigned to the variable as a list:</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">Assign the rest of the values as a list called \"red\":</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">fruits = (<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"apple\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"banana\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"cherry\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"strawberry\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"raspberry\"</span>)<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span>(green, yellow, *red) = fruits<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(green)<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(yellow)<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(red)<br></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"https://www.w3schools.com/python/trypython.asp?filename=demo_tuple_unpacking_asterix1\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Try it Yourself »</a></div><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">If the asterisk is added to another variable name than the last, Python will assign values to the variable until the number of values left matches the number of variables left.</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">Add a list of values the \"tropic\" variable:</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">fruits = (<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"apple\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"mango\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"papaya\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"pineapple\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"cherry\"</span>)<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span>(green, *tropic, red) = fruits<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(green)<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(tropic)<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(red)<br></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"https://www.w3schools.com/python/trypython.asp?filename=demo_tuple_unpacking_asterix2\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Try it Yourself »</a></div>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2023-06-15 13:10:20'),
