oop.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">The \"inner loop\" will be executed one time for each iteration of the \"outer loop\":</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">Print each adjective for every fruit:</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">adj = [<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"red\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"big\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"tasty\"</span>]<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">fruits = [<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"apple\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"banana\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"cherry\"</span>]<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">for</span>&nbsp;x&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">in</span>&nbsp;adj:<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">for</span>&nbsp;y&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">in</span>&nbsp;fruits:<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(x, y)<br></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"https://www.w3schools.com/python/trypython.asp?filename=demo_for_nested\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Try it Yourself »</a></div><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The pass Statement</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 15.75px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3);\">for</code>&nbsp;loops cannot be empty, but if you for some reason have a&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 15.75px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3);\">for</code>&nbsp;loop with no content, put in the&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 15.75px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3);\">pass</code>&nbsp;statement to avoid getting an error.</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example</h3><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">for</span>&nbsp;x&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">in</span>&nbsp;[<span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\">0</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\">1</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\">2</span>]:<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">pass</span><br></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"https://www.w3schools.com/python/trypython.asp?filename=demo_for_pass\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Try it Yourself »</a></div></div>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2023-06-15 14:02:26');
INSERT INTO `questions_learn` (`id`, `title`, `slug`, `description`, `codes`, `search_count`, `is_input_required`, `updated_at`, `created_at`) VALUES
(54, 'Python Functions', 'python-functions', '<p class=\"intro\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">A function is a block of code which only runs when it is called.</p><p class=\"intro\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">You can pass data, known as parameters, into a function.</p><p class=\"intro\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">A function can return data as a result.</p><hr style=\"margin-right: -16px; margin-left: -16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Creating a Function</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">In Python a function is defined using the&nbsp;<span class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 15.75px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3); padding-left: 4px; padding-right: 4px;\">def</span>&nbsp;keyword:</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example<br></h3><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">def</span>&nbsp;my_function():<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"Hello from a function\"</span>)<br></div></div><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Calling a Function</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">To call a function, use the function name followed by parenthesis:</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example</h3><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">def</span>&nbsp;my_function():<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"Hello from a function\"</span>)<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bolder;\">my_function()</span><br></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"https://www.w3schools.com/python/trypython.asp?filename=demo_function\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Try it Yourself »</a></div><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Arguments</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">Information can be passed into functions as arguments.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">Arguments are specified after the function name, inside the parentheses. You can add as many arguments as you want, just separate them with a comma.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">The following example has a function with one argument (fname). When the function is called, we pass along a first name, which is used inside the function to print the full name:</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example</h3><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">def</span>&nbsp;my_function(<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bolder;\">fname</span>):<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(fname +&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\" Refsnes\"</span>)<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span>my_function(<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bolder;\"><span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"Emil\"</span></span>)<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">my_function(<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bolder;\"><span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"Tobias\"</span></span>)<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">my_function(<span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bolder;\"><span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"Linus\"</span></span>)<br></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"https://www.w3schools.com/python/trypython.asp?filename=demo_function_param\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Try it Yourself »</a></div><div class=\"w3-panel w3-note\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; padding: 16px 32px; margin: 24px -32px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 204); border-left: none; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Arguments</em>&nbsp;are often shortened to&nbsp;<em style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">args</em>&nbsp;in Python documentations.</p></div><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Parameters or Arguments?</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">The terms&nbsp;<em style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">parameter</em>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<em style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">argument</em>&nbsp;can be used for the same thing: information that are passed into a function.</p><div class=\"w3-panel w3-note\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; padding: 16px 32px; margin: 24px -32px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 204); border-left: none; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">From a function\'s perspective:</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">A parameter is the variable listed inside the parentheses in the function definition.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">An argument is the value that is sent to the function when it is called.</p></div><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Number of Arguments</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">By default, a function must be called with the correct number of arguments. Meaning that if your function expects 2 arguments, you have to call the function with 2 arguments, not more, and not less.</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">This function expects 2 arguments, and gets 2 arguments:</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">def</span>&nbsp;my_function(fname, lname):<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(fname +&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\" \"</span>&nbsp;+ lname)<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span>my_function(<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"Emil\"</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"Refsnes\"</span>)<br></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"https://www.w3schools.com/python/trypython.asp?filename=demo_function_args_n\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Try it Yourself »</a></div><p><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">If you try to call the function with 1 or 3 arguments, you will get an error:</span></p><div class=\"w3-example w3-pale-red\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">This function expects 2 arguments, but gets only 1:</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh w3-border-red\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px 