(65, 'Python JSON', 'python-json', '<p class=\"intro\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">JSON is a syntax for storing and exchanging data.</p><p class=\"intro\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">JSON is text, written with JavaScript object notation.</p><hr style=\"margin-right: -16px; margin-left: -16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">JSON in Python</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">Python has a built-in package called&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 15.75px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3);\">json</code>, which can be used to work with JSON data.</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example<br></h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">Import the json module:</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">import</span>&nbsp;json<br></div></div><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Parse JSON - Convert from JSON to Python</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">If you have a JSON string, you can parse it by using the&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 15.75px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3);\">json.loads()</code>&nbsp;method.</p><div class=\"w3-panel w3-note\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; padding: 16px 32px; margin: 24px -32px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 204); border-left: none; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">The result will be a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.w3schools.com/python/python_dictionaries.asp\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: inherit;\">Python dictionary</a>.</p></div><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">Convert from JSON to Python:</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">import</span>&nbsp;json<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"commentcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: green;\"># some JSON:<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"></span>x =&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\'{ \"name\":\"John\", \"age\":30, \"city\":\"New York\"}\'</span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"commentcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: green;\"># parse x:<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"></span>y = json.loads(x)<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"commentcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: green;\"># the result is a Python dictionary:<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"></span><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(y[<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"age\"</span>])<br></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"https://www.w3schools.com/python/trypython.asp?filename=demo_json\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Try it Yourself »</a></div><h2 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 32px; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Convert from Python to JSON</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">If you have a Python object, you can convert it into a JSON string by using the&nbsp;<code class=\"w3-codespan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; font-size: 15.75px; color: crimson; background-color: rgba(222, 222, 222, 0.3);\">json.dumps()</code>&nbsp;method.</p><div class=\"w3-example\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(231, 233, 235); border-radius: 5px; padding: 8px 20px; margin: 24px -20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Example</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;\">Convert from Python to JSON:</p><div class=\"w3-code notranslate pythonHigh\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Menlo, &quot;courier new&quot;, monospace; width: auto; background-color: rgb(21, 32, 43); color: white; padding: 8px 12px; border-left: 4px solid rgb(40, 44, 52); overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 16px !important; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\"><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">import</span>&nbsp;json<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"commentcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: green;\"># a Python object (dict):<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"></span>x = {<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"name\"</span>:&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span><span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"John\"</span>,<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"age\"</span>:&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\">30</span>,<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"city\"</span>:&nbsp;<span class=\"pythonstringcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: brown;\">\"New York\"</span><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">}<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"commentcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: green;\"># convert into JSON:<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"></span>y = json.dumps(x)<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"><span class=\"commentcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: green;\"># the result is a JSON string:<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\"></span><span class=\"pythonnumbercolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: red;\"></span><span class=\"pythonkeywordcolor\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: mediumblue;\">print</span>(y)<br></div><a target=\"_blank\" class=\"w3-btn w3-margin-bottom\" href=\"https://www.w3schools.com/python/trypython.asp?filename=demo_json_from_python\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: rgb(76, 175, 80); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: none; display: inline-block; padding: 6px 18px; vertical-align: middle; overflow: hidden; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; text-wrap: nowrap; user-select: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 17px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 16px !important;\">Try it Yourself »</a></div><div><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 1.2em; font-size: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">You can convert Pytho